Explanation:

The solution iterates through the digits of the number using a while loop. In each iteration, it extracts the last digit using the modulo operator (%), adds it to the sum, and removes the last digit by dividing the number by 10. This process continues until the number becomes 0, at which point it returns the sum of the digits. The time complexity is O(log(n)) because the loop iterates log(n) times, where n is the number of digits in the input number. The space complexity is O(1) because the algorithm uses a constant amount of space to store the sum. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not require any additional resources beyond the standard Java runtime environment.

